Enzo.note: Enzo is one of the only three irregular verbs in Natalician.

A.description: Marks a declarative sentence as a binary (yes/no) question.
A.examples: A kelšedi Natal? (Do you speak Natalicican?)

Ački.examples: Ački berrek körkesi anlaso (Whichever car moves first)

Ačküz.examples: Serševi ek ačküz dirtis (Whoever did it has to fix it)

Anlaso.examples: Anlaso hasman forzaro (first start the engine)

Ädres.examples: Fas in ädres un (Give me your address)

Äg.examples:
1. A endei äg Könek? (Are you with Könek?)
2. Äg in ianzak (I have food)
Äg.note: Äg + pronoun/object + subject makes a possessive sentence. See example 2.

Ägde.examples:
1. Mah ägde cul (Water without food)
2. Ägde süs berrek (He does not have a car)
